The 60's music and peace movement may have contributed to a global
consciousness, but the seeds were already planted by many others who came
before.
You can go as far back as 2000 years and find a universal message of love
and goodwill in Christ's teachings.  The song &quot;The Word&quot; seems like Lennon's
interpretation of the opening verses of the Gospel of John.  The heavy
emphasis on love echoes the message already found in the 3 epistles of  John
in the New Testament. Woodrow Wilson's League of Nations and later the
United Nations need to be factored in as more influential than the Beatles.
Henry David Thoreau's writings sparked a lot of debate on the roll of
citizenry and were influential as well.
